<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-06-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-06-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="684" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d684">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 815.001 B 46/2.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">American Minister</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 141.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-06-16">
                                    <hi rend="italic">June 16, 1913</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I inclose, with office copy, a letter
                            addressed by the President to His Excellency Francisco Bertrand,<note n="1" xml:id="d684fn1">Not printed.</note> acknowledging His
                            Excellency’s letter of April 1 last in which he announced his assumption
                            on March 21 last of the Presidency of the Republic of Honduras and his
                            entrance upon the duties of that office.</p>
                        <p>You will forward the copy to the Foreign Office and deliver the original
                            in the manner most agreeable to His Excellency.</p>
                        <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>For the Secretary of State: <lb/>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">J. B. Moore</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>